* getElementById() = If the tag we need has an id attribute, we can get it by calling the getElementById()

document.getElementById("userName");

* querySelector() = With the querySelector() method it is possible to return the first document element
that corresponds to the specified selector:

var speed = document.querySelector("div");

* querySelectorAll() = querySelectorAll() gets all elements that match the specified selector.
Do not forget that there are class selectors (".className"), id ("#idName") selectors and many others.
All of them can be used in the methods of querySelectorAll() and querySelector().

let restaurant = document.querySelectorAll(".menu");
let streets = document.querySelectorAll(".street");
